## v1.4 — Watchtower-driven response loop (2026-05-09)

**Trigger:** Jeffrey Emanuel comments on any of our open issues at
github.com/Dicklesworthstone (search axis: `author:JYeswak owner:Dicklesworthstone`).

**Old failure mode:** the orchestrator only noticed Jeffrey replies when
Joshua manually surfaced "is anything we need to add?" That is not the
system. Today's audit found 7 open Jeffrey issues all replied to via
flywheel-e150e but only AFTER manual Joshua surfacing.

**New mechanical surface:** `.flywheel/scripts/jeffrey-comment-watchtower.sh`
+ `~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.zeststream.jeffrey-comment-watchtower.plist`
poll every 15 minutes, append unseen Jeffrey comments to
`~/.local/state/flywheel/jeffrey-comment-watchtower.jsonl`, and dispatch
a `JEFFREY_COMMENT_NEW` signal to the flywheel orchestrator pane.

### Signal shape

```text
JEFFREY_COMMENT_NEW repo=<owner/repo> issue=#<n> comment_id=<id> excerpt="<first-150-chars-scrubbed>" action=reply-required
```

### Orchestrator obligations on receipt

1. **File a reply-bead within 30 minutes of receipt** (per L70
   ORCH-NO-PUNT and the new L151 JEFFREY-COMMENT-RESPONSE-SLA).
   Priority P1, labels `jeff-issue-chain,reply-required,<repo>`.
2. **Ship reply within 4 waking hours** of comment landing. If the
   comment lands outside waking hours, the SLA window starts at the
   next waking hour.
3. **Reply text is Joshua-approved** — the watchtower DETECTS and
   DISPATCHES; Joshua disposes the reply text. Auto-replying without
   human review is forbidden.
4. **Reply runs the v1.1 + v1.2 disposition tables.** Pick a side per
   Shape-5 design-collab when applicable. Use `Jeffrey`, not `Jeff`,
   in human-facing prose.

### v1.4 disposition extension — CONFIRM-CONTRACT

| Shape | Signal | Action |
|---|---|---|
| 6. **CONFIRM-CONTRACT** (v1.4 addition) | Jeffrey replies with a contract sketch already approximating our wrapper-parity ask | Confirm the field shape works for our flow, run a dogfood probe locally if installable, post the receipt and close-out language. Do not introduce new asks unless they're load-bearing — preserve the contract Jeffrey shipped. |

### Watchtower operational notes

- **Bootstrap (first install):** run
  `.flywheel/scripts/jeffrey-comment-watchtower.sh --reseed --apply`
  ONCE to mark every existing Jeffrey comment as seen. Otherwise the
  first launchd run will dispatch every existing Jeffrey comment as
  if new (false-positive storm).
- **launchd lifecycle:**
  ```bash
  launchctl bootstrap gui/$UID ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.zeststream.jeffrey-comment-watchtower.plist
  launchctl print gui/$UID/ai.zeststream.jeffrey-comment-watchtower
  launchctl bootout gui/$UID/ai.zeststream.jeffrey-comment-watchtower   # on retire/rotate
  ```
- **Cadence is 15 minutes.** That's the polling cadence; the SLA is
  4 waking hours. The 15-minute cadence guarantees worst-case detect-
  to-dispatch latency stays inside the receipt budget.
- **Heartbeat log:** every run writes one row to
  `~/.local/logs/jeffrey-comment-watchtower.jsonl` with
  `mode={run|dry-run|reseed}`, `new_count`, `poll_count`, `status`,
  and `error` (empty when clean).
- **Doctor:** `--doctor --json` returns `status=ok` when `gh`, `jq`,
  `perl`, `ntm`, ledger directory writability, and `gh auth status`
  all pass.
- **Re-enable after rotation:** if CAAM rotation or fleet respawn
  unloads the plist, re-run `launchctl bootstrap` from the lifecycle
  block above.

